<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[869,1493,218,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,993,218,243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[1005,1239,218,243]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1005,1239,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Canthon cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1340,218,243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<emphasis box="[949,1198,250,275]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[949,1194,250,275]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">Canthon ibarragrassoi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with which it shares the metafemora with a sinuous carina close to the anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[964,1028,314,339]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="4.[170,229,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[171,790,1554,2043]" captionTargetId="figure-544@4.[170,793,1553,2044]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 3. Metafemur, ventral view of (A) Canthon cleidecostae; and (B) Canthon ibarragrassoi.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615090/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, it can be easily separated by the clypeal teeth, which are U-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[909,992,378,403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and V-shaped in 
<emphasis box="[1179,1351,378,403]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1179,1347,378,403]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">C. ibarragrassoi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The colour is also characteristic while 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[1136,1292,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1136,1292,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1297,1379,410,435]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is metallic green and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[988,1153,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">
<emphasis box="[988,1153,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C. ibarragrassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
present black colouration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[869,1494,506,787]" lastBlockId="3.[794,1419,218,851]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1218,506,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Description (
<typeStatus box="[1021,1134,506,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Holotype</typeStatus>
, Male):
</emphasis>
Dorsal habitus (
<figureCitation box="[1403,1481,506,531]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" captionTargetId="figure-286@2.[170,1493,829,2076]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Canthon cleidecostae sp.nov.:(A) dorsal;(B) ventral;and (C) lateral view;(D) head,dorsal view.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Body length (except the head) 
<quantity box="[1201,1298,538,563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="7.55">7.55 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1306,1375,538,563]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Head:</emphasis>
dorsal surface slightly concave with green alveolar microsculpture; posterior half with finely spaced punctation and anteri- or half with superficial rugosities. Two triangular clypeal teeth, with rounded apex, separated by a U-shaped emargination (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1105,698,723]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" captionTargetId="figure-286@2.[170,1493,829,2076]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Canthon cleidecostae sp.nov.:(A) dorsal;(B) ventral;and (C) lateral view;(D) head,dorsal view.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Clypeal margin and lateral margin of head with yellow setae emanating from underneath. Clypeo-genal suture present and oblique until close to eyes. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[158,284,218,243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pronotum:</emphasis>
pronotal disc smooth, metallic green, bright with green alveolar microsculpture. Anterior angles acute, pointed forward (
<figureCitation box="[441,525,282,307]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" captionTargetId="figure-286@2.[170,1493,829,2076]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Canthon cleidecostae sp.nov.:(A) dorsal;(B) ventral;and (C) lateral view;(D) head,dorsal view.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Lateral margin smooth with two little teeth and brief emargination between them (more visible in lateral view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[571,718,346,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hypomeron:</emphasis>
dark green, with coriarious microsculpture, sparse yellowish setae anteriorly, and thin transverse carina at centre not touching lateral margin; anterior region slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[199,274,474,499]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" captionTargetId="figure-286@2.[170,1493,829,2076]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Canthon cleidecostae sp.nov.:(A) dorsal;(B) ventral;and (C) lateral view;(D) head,dorsal view.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[292,368,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Elytra:</emphasis>
surface with dark green colour, less bright than pronotum; with fine micropuncture. Striae narrow and poorly visible, with punctation; interstriae wide, flat. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[271,333,570,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Legs:</emphasis>
protibiae with three main teeth on outer edge and crenulated until the base; protibial spur flattened dorsoventrally, bifid, asymmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[622,709,634,659]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[94,1413,882,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-360@3.[94,1417,878,2012]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Details of structure in Canthon cleidecostae sp. nov.: (A) male protibial apex, dorsal; Male genitalia: (B) aedeagus, lateral; internal sac: (C) dorsal and (D) ventral views;internal sac apical and parietal sclerites:(E) dorsal and (F) ventral views [Ax= axial sclerite;FLP = fronto-lateral peripheric sclerite;MP = medial peripheric sclerite;SA = subaxial sclerite;SRP = superior peripheric sclerite].Black arrow showing the semiduct.Scale bars:A-D = 1 mm; E and F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Mesofemora with ventral side lacking anterior and posterior margin. Metafemora subclaviform, with a sinuous carina (
<figureCitation box="[174,252,730,755]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="4.[170,229,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[171,790,1554,2043]" captionTargetId="figure-544@4.[170,793,1553,2044]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 3. Metafemur, ventral view of (A) Canthon cleidecostae; and (B) Canthon ibarragrassoi.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615090/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, white setae); yellow setae on the anterior edge and close to apex; posterior edge with lobe comprising two-thirds apically (
<figureCitation box="[404,486,794,819]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="4.[170,229,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[171,790,1554,2043]" captionTargetId="figure-544@4.[170,793,1553,2044]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 3. Metafemur, ventral view of (A) Canthon cleidecostae; and (B) Canthon ibarragrassoi.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615090/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[505,629,794,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Abdomen:</emphasis>
surface with alveolar microsculpture; dark green. Ventrites with tufts of small yellow setae on each side laterally and medially glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[947,1022,250,275]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" captionTargetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" captionTargetId="figure-286@2.[170,1493,829,2076]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Canthon cleidecostae sp.nov.:(A) dorsal;(B) ventral;and (C) lateral view;(D) head,dorsal view.Scale bar:1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1041,1160,250,275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pygidium:</emphasis>
as wide as long; bright green without punctation. Basal margin expanded, forming strongV-shaped carina between pygidium and propygidium. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[883,1015,346,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Parameres:</emphasis>
lateral view: symmetrical; apex truncate (
<figureCitation box="[851,927,378,403]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[94,1413,882,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-360@3.[94,1417,878,2012]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Details of structure in Canthon cleidecostae sp. nov.: (A) male protibial apex, dorsal; Male genitalia: (B) aedeagus, lateral; internal sac: (C) dorsal and (D) ventral views;internal sac apical and parietal sclerites:(E) dorsal and (F) ventral views [Ax= axial sclerite;FLP = fronto-lateral peripheric sclerite;MP = medial peripheric sclerite;SA = subaxial sclerite;SRP = superior peripheric sclerite].Black arrow showing the semiduct.Scale bars:A-D = 1 mm; E and F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Superior edge straight and inferior concave, never sinuous. Apical-laterally edge with bulge at centre. Dorsal view: membranous portion separating parameres from base to apex. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1147,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Internal sac:</emphasis>
peripheral fronto-lateral sclerite (FLP) connected to of the axial sclerite (Ax), both sclerites forming an apical complex, in which Ax forms a central semiduct (
<figureCitation box="[991,1065,570,595]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[94,1413,882,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-360@3.[94,1417,878,2012]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Details of structure in Canthon cleidecostae sp. nov.: (A) male protibial apex, dorsal; Male genitalia: (B) aedeagus, lateral; internal sac: (C) dorsal and (D) ventral views;internal sac apical and parietal sclerites:(E) dorsal and (F) ventral views [Ax= axial sclerite;FLP = fronto-lateral peripheric sclerite;MP = medial peripheric sclerite;SA = subaxial sclerite;SRP = superior peripheric sclerite].Black arrow showing the semiduct.Scale bars:A-D = 1 mm; E and F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
, Ax [black arrow]) and FLP completes the circunference in the semiduct (Ax) (like a roof), base and apex of all the complexes of equal size, without tapered region; subaxial sclerite (SA), about the same size as other sclerites, covering ventrally the FLP + Ax complex; peripheral medial sclerite (MP) flat, rolled, with the basal part more acute (in relation to the apex), lateral in relation to FLP + Ax; superior right peripheral sclerite (SRP) with lateral angular prolongation (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1298,826,851]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[94,153,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[94,1413,882,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-360@3.[94,1417,878,2012]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Details of structure in Canthon cleidecostae sp. nov.: (A) male protibial apex, dorsal; Male genitalia: (B) aedeagus, lateral; internal sac: (C) dorsal and (D) ventral views;internal sac apical and parietal sclerites:(E) dorsal and (F) ventral views [Ax= axial sclerite;FLP = fronto-lateral peripheric sclerite;MP = medial peripheric sclerite;SA = subaxial sclerite;SRP = superior peripheric sclerite].Black arrow showing the semiduct.Scale bars:A-D = 1 mm; E and F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
E-F).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615080" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4615080" box="[170,1262,2106,2131]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" startId="2.[170,229,2106,2131]" targetBox="[174,1492,830,2073]" targetPageId="2">
