<paragraph blockId="4.[170,794,218,339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,471,218,243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Morphological variation:</emphasis>
The variation between the two specimens of the type series is centred on the body length, which varied from 
<quantity box="[539,638,282,307]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="6.05">6.05 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus box="[653,756,282,307]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">paratype</typeStatus>
) to 
<quantity box="[170,266,314,339]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="7.55">7.55 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus box="[279,384,314,339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,795,378,563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,306,378,403]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species is named after Dr. Cleide Costa, in acknowledgement of her great contribution to the study of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[271,394,442,467]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
and for supervising many Brazilian coleopterists. An important remark is that the larva of this species is still unknown and we hope it will be described in collaboration with Dr. Costa when available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,794,602,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,321,602,627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Distribution:</emphasis>
So far, this species is only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[170,220,634,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
locality (Monte Alegre de 
<collectingRegion box="[509,573,634,659]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[581,704,634,659]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation box="[722,783,634,659]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="4.[869,928,1047,1072]" captionTargetBox="[873,1491,207,1014]" captionTargetId="figure-503@4.[869,1493,204,1017]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 4. The distribution record of Canthon cleidecostae sp. nov., central Brazil [TO = Tocantins;MT = Mato Grosso;GO = Goiás;DF = Distrito Federal; BA = Bahia;MG = Minas Gerais;MS = Mato Grosso do Sul]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615086/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,794,698,915]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,261,698,723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Biology</emphasis>
: Nothing is known about the biology of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[170,329,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[170,329,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[337,424,730,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The feeding habits are probably coprophagous, considering related species of the same genus. Besides, the type-series was collected in 
<taxonomicName authority="Moojen, Locks &amp; Langguth, 1997" authorityName="Moojen, Locks &amp; Langguth" authorityYear="1997" class="Mammalia" family="Caviidae" genus="Kerodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acrobata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Kerodon acrobata</emphasis>
Moojen, Locks &amp; Langguth, 1997
</taxonomicName>
faeces, a rodent endemic of 
<collectingCountry box="[375,435,858,883]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and know only to 
<collectingRegion box="[667,794,858,883]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Woods, C. A. &amp; Kilpatrick, C. W." box="[176,457,890,915]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1538 - 1600" refId="ref4669" refString="Woods, C. A. &amp; Kilpatrick, C. W. 2005. Infraorder Hystricognathi. In: Wilson, D. E. &amp; Reeder, D. M. (Eds.). Mammal Species of the World: A taxonomic and geographic reference. 3. ed. Baltimore, Johns Hopkins University Press. v. 2, p. 1538 - 1600." type="journal article" year="2005">Woods &amp; Kilpatrick, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,795,954,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,305,954,979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Comments:</emphasis>
The placement of this new species within the subgenera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffmannsegg" authorityYear="1817" box="[373,466,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,466,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still uncertain. Some morphological characteristics used to describe this species are similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martinez, 1952)" baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[342,791,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">
<emphasis box="[342,587,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon ibarragrassoi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, A." box="[607,785,1050,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="53 - 118" refId="ref4011" refString="Martinez, A. 1952. Scarabaeidae nuevos o poco conocidos, III. Mision de Estudios de Patologia regional argentina, 23 (81 - 82): 53 - 118." type="journal article" year="1952">Martínez, 1952</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, mainly considering the sinuous carina in the metafemur.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4615086" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4615086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4615086/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" startId="4.[869,928,1047,1072]" targetBox="[873,1491,207,1014]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[869,1494,1047,1136]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figure 4. The distribution record of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[1183,1353,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1183,1353,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1427,1047,1072]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, central Brazil [TO = Tocantins;MT = Mato Grosso;GO = Goiás;DF = Distrito Federal; BA = Bahia;MG = Minas Gerais;MS = Mato Grosso do Sul].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,795,954,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The geographic distribution of both species is distinct. 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[233,462,1146,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[233,462,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[468,553,1146,1171]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known for the 
<typeStatus box="[744,794,1146,1171]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
locality as aforementioned, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[553,793,1178,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">
<emphasis box="[553,793,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon ibarragrassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded to 
<collectingCountry box="[334,437,1210,1235]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[451,503,1210,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
locality: Colonia Natalício Talavera), 
<collectingCountry box="[280,390,1242,1267]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[401,674,1242,1267]" name="Mesopotamia Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Mesopotamia Argentina</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[734,794,1242,1267]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[176,391,1274,1299]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[404,572,1274,1299]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[585,663,1274,1299]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[676,791,1274,1299]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[170,401,1306,1331]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[415,581,1306,1331]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[595,741,1306,1331]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[170,323,1338,1363]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Espirito Santo</collectingRegion>
states, the latter state being the northernmost known record of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[170,795,954,1491]" lastBlockId="4.[869,1494,1210,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
As currently understood, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[515,688,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">
<emphasis box="[515,688,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. ibarragrassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="1948" box="[383,572,1434,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Glaphyrocanthon">
<emphasis box="[383,572,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Glaphyrocanthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considering many characteristics listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Halffter, G. &amp; Martinez, A." box="[447,791,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="29 - 107" refId="ref3798" refString="Halffter, G. &amp; Martinez, A. 1977. Revision monografica de los Canthonina americanos, IV parte. Clave para generos y subgeneros. Folia EntomolOgica Mexicana, 38: 29 - 107." type="journal article" year="1977">Halffter &amp; Martínez (1977: 79)</bibRefCitation>
. However, even 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[1054,1217,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1054,1217,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1231,1323,1210,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
sharing these characteristics with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1120,1299,1242,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibarragrassoi">
<emphasis box="[1120,1299,1242,1267]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C. ibarragrassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we concluded that the new species should not be included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="1948" box="[869,1058,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Glaphyrocanthon">
<emphasis box="[869,1058,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Glaphyrocanthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without a detailed taxonomic revision of this subgenus. Thus, to avoid “taxonomic instability”, we regard 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[986,1216,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[986,1216,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1221,1305,1370,1395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as 
<emphasis box="[1339,1489,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">incertae sedis.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[869,1494,1210,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
In addition, the sclerites of the internal sac are not similar to those found in 
<emphasis box="[1223,1378,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Goniocanthon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, A. &amp; Pereira, F. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="363 - 388" refId="ref4064" refString="Martinez, A. &amp; Pereira, F. S. 1956. Dois generos novos de Canthonini americanos (Col. Scarabaeoidea, Scarabaeidae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, Sao Paulo, 12: 363 - 388." type="journal article" year="1956">Pereira &amp; Martínez, 1956</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, L. G. de &amp; Nunes, R. V. &amp; Vaz-de-Mello, F. Z." box="[1051,1258,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref4105" refString="Nunes, L. G. de O. A.; Nunes, R. V. &amp; Vaz-de-Mello, F. Z. 2018. Taxonomic revision of the South American subgenus Canthon (Pelthecanthon) Pereira, 1953 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae: Deltochilini). European Journal of Taxonomy, 437: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2018">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[1132,1191,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.,</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), nor in 
<emphasis box="[1352,1493,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Peltecanthon</emphasis>
(Nunes 
<emphasis box="[959,1021,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.,</emphasis>
in press), where the Ax + FLP complex gradually tapers to a much thinner apex, or even other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffmannsegg" authorityYear="1817" box="[869,962,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[869,962,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
handled by one of the authors (Nunes, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">personal remarks</emphasis>
). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva, 2020" authorityName="Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Nunes &amp; Costa-Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[1002,1231,1594,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cleidecostae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1002,1231,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Canthon cleidecostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1236,1322,1594,1619]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the apex is not thin, something similar to that observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Blanchard, 1845" authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Tetraechma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1366,1493,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Tetraechma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard, C. E." box="[869,1047,1658,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="155 - 168" refId="ref3633" refString="Blanchard, C. E. 1845. Insectes de l'Amerique Meridionale. In: d'Orbigny, A.; Blanchard, C. E. &amp; Brulle, A. Voyage dans l'Amerique Meridionale, Insectes Coleopteres. Tribu des Lamellicornes Paris, P. Bertrand. v. 6, pt 2, p. 155 - 168." type="book chapter" year="1845">Blanchard, 1845</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Nunes, 
<emphasis box="[1141,1325,1658,1683]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">personal remarks</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
